{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bdc2f6da-1f89-4581-b9b1-1a123e68b06b","content":"\n\nIn .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle events API** in `MauiProgram.cs` (or your app builder setup) via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the activity is pausing\n        })\n        .OnStop(activity =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the activity is no longer visible\n        }));\n#endif\n\n#if IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the app enters background\n        }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` is called on the `MauiAppBuilder`.\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#if IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code separated.\n- Each platform exposes its native events (e.g., `OnResume`, `OnDestroy` for Android; `WillEnterForeground`, `WillTerminate` for iOS).\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` for the extension methods.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9c525261-eb1e-4fad-a5cc-759e1bfb9e1e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's `OnPause`/`OnStop` and iOS's `DidEnterBackground`. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase task.","outputTokens":398},"id":"4e1b5d4d-af97-4e91-8faa-ed34010feba5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:49:12.791Z","parentId":"5c453352-db1a-4744-9289-322ee6801a14"}
